Chrysippus furthermore declares that, if there be no gods, the natural universe contains nothing superior to man ; but for any man to think that there is nothing superior to man he deems to be the height of arrogance. Let us grant that it is a mark of arrogance to value oneself more highly than the world ; but not merely is it not a mark of arro- gance, rather is it a mark of wisdom, to realize that one is a conscious and rational being, and that Orion and Canicula are not.
